    {
        "content": "<p>i'm guessing the issue is the way the multiplications are bracketed</p>",
        "id": 492487240,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1736336774
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i.e. the expression it is searching in is <code>(a * r ^ (↑m + 1)) * r</code>, which doesn't match. rewriting using <code>mul_assoc</code> should fix it</p>",
        "id": 492487431,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1736336856
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>also, there is no <code>zpow</code> used, so the right lemma to use would be <code>pow_succ r (m + 1)</code></p>",
        "id": 492488053,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1736337110
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"577757\">Icaro Costa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Lean.20can't.20find.20pattern.20to.20rewrite/near/492485806\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>r ^ (↑m + 1) * r</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Notice the \\uparrow: it is a coercion to Int, while the expression (m + 1) in your goal is a Nat.</p>",
        "id": 492488646,
        "sender_full_name": "Vlad Tsyrklevich",
        "timestamp": 1736337341
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Alright, <code>rw[mul_assoc, ← pow_succ r (m+1)]</code> did the trick. Thanks</p>",
